
🚀 Overview

This project focuses on building a data-driven system for predicting product demand and optimizing inventory levels.

Businesses often suffer from overstocking (wasted capital) or stockouts (lost sales). Traditional forecasting methods fail to capture complex demand patterns.

This project uses Machine Learning and Time-Series models to improve prediction accuracy and support smarter inventory decisions.

🎯 Objectives
Predict future product demand accurately
Minimize inventory holding and shortage costs
Automate decision-making using data insights
Build a scalable solution for real-world businesses
🛠️ Project Workflow
1. Data Collection & Preprocessing
Collected historical sales data
Merged inventory and product datasets
Handled missing values and inconsistencies
Generated a structured dataset for analysis
2. Demand Forecasting
Applied feature engineering (lag features, rolling mean)
Implemented forecasting models:
Random Forest
ARIMA
LSTM
Evaluated performance using:
MAE (Mean Absolute Error)
RMSE (Root Mean Squared Error)

👉 Output: Forecasted Demand

3. Inventory Optimization
Calculated Economic Order Quantity (EOQ)
Estimated Safety Stock
Determined Reorder Point

👉 Goal: Minimize inventory cost while maintaining availability
👉 Output: Optimal Inventory Levels

4. Performance Evaluation
Compared Actual vs Predicted Demand
Evaluated cost efficiency
Analyzed inventory turnover

👉 Output: Actionable Business Insights

5. Visualization & Deployment
Built dashboards for:
Demand forecasting
Inventory status
Alerts and insights
Tools used:
Streamlit
Power BI

👉 Output: Decision Support System

